an><hr size=1>   Part of the reason Raids sometime get dull is because they become so predictable. Detailed maps of dungeons are easily obtained online as well as complete MOB listings that include MOB HP, spawn rate, and drops. <br>
  <br>
  Want to do a raid where there are NO maps found on EQAtlas and MOBs and encounters are random generated? If this sounds interesting to you I have a proposal.<br>
 <br>
  After talking to a few people in Guild a few of us decided to plan a RL raid on Vegas. Thought it might be nice to meet some of the people we spend so much time talking to. Though nothing is set in stone it is currently being planned for June to accommodate those taking classes. <br>
<br>
  Ones I have talked to that have shown interest are Dadijob, LLuyen, Eorgal(?) Valmar, Chandora, Leana and myself.  Hope to see many more you there as well. Hoping to be able to get together at least for a dinner. Afterwards we could split up and camp different spawns appropriate to the different levels (age) and taste (or lack of) of guild members attending.   <br>
<br>
   Please let me know if you are interested. Open to suggestions for alternate locations or timeframe. <br>
<br>
   Words of advice <br>
   1) Vegas dungeon is heavily camped for the phat loot that is sometimes dropped there so advance booking is recommended.<br>
   2) EQAtlas does not provide maps of this dungeon.  <br>
   3) Generic MOBs are random so there is no listing of their exp value or drops.<br>
   4) Named MOBS for each location are listed but are often heavily camped.   <br>
   5) Many GMs (Game Masters) can be found there and are easily identified.<br>
   6) There is a slight twist to the Plane level requirement format. Anyone of any level(age) can go there but many individual camps within have level requirements. <br>
   7) Another twist is that previously you took Wizards to go see the planes. Here it is reversed; you take planes to go to see Wizards. <br>
   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Another new enhancement being tried here is the introduction of merchants found at almost every location. <br>
Difference is that most only deal with selling their wares. If you want to sell your wares you must look for merchants that are setup for this purpose. These merchants are named in honor of the popularity of the giant Chessboard found in Butcherblock and are referred to as Pawn brokers.<br>
   9) Highly recommended to take gear that boosts Magic Resistance. Rumors prevail of wandering enchanter class mobs that possess an innate hypnotism ability to cast Charm, Mez and Illusionary beauty to lure unsuspecting PCs to their lair. These Mobs have been named A Hypnotic Overlord (HO) and often cast a delayed DOT that can cause disease long after the encounter. Many more unconfirmed reports of MOBs casting a wide-range AOE debuff that drastically lowers the PCs intelligence.  <br>
<br>
  Hope to see everyone there<br>
